 1.0  ->  Requirements
 2.0  ->  Installation
 3.0  ->  Modules

(1.0) Requirements
================================================================================
ghc     - http://haskell.org/ghc/
git     - http://git-scm.com


(2.0) Installation
================================================================================
Configure it for global installation:
 $ runhaskell Setup configure
Or for a local installation:
 $ runhaskell Setup configure --prefix=$HOME --user

Build:
 $ runhaskell Setup build

Install:
 $ runhaskell Setup install

Execute:
 $ rivertam (You can find the binary file in the PREFIX directory or in the /usr/local/bin directory.)

NOTE: Example configs are in the data directory.
NOTE: River-Tam will automatically copy river.conf to the config directory at the first startup.


(3.0) Modules
================================================================================
List of Modules:
 1. Tremulous    = notrem   - Commands are: find, poll, listplayers, onlineclans
 2. ClanWar      = nocw     - Commands are: cw-addgame, cw-detailed, cw-lastgame, cw-listopponents
 3. Flame/Love   = noflame  - Commands are: flameadd, loveadd, flame, love

Excluding modules:
 $ runhaskell Setup build --ghc-options="-Dno<name-of-module>"

Examples:
# Building without any modules:
 $ runhaskell Setup build --ghc-options="-Dnotrem -Dnocw -Dnoflame"
# Building with all modules except ClanWar
 $ runhaskell Setup build --ghc-options="-Dnocw"
# Building with all modules
 $ runhaskell Setup build

NOTE: All modules will be installed by default.
NOTE: Don't forget to reinstall it. (Instructions at 2.0)
